# PRD: Shared Asset Library (Client & Consultant Access)

## Product
Superwork – Client Portal

## Feature Name
Shared Asset Library

## Status
Proposed

## Owner
Superwork Product

## Last Updated
2026-02-06

---

## 1. Problem Statement

Clients and consultants currently lack a single, structured place to store and access shared assets such as:
- Brand images and logos
- PDFs (brand guidelines, pitch decks, brochures)
- Fonts (for design and ad work)

Assets are today shared ad hoc via email, Google Drive, Slack, or WeTransfer, which leads to:
- Version confusion
- Missing or outdated files
- Time wasted asking for access
- Assets being lost between projects

This creates friction in delivery and slows down execution.

---

## 2. Goal

Create a **Shared Asset Library** where:
- Clients can upload and manage their assets
- Consultants can access and use the same assets
- All files are stored centrally in **Supabase Storage**
- Access is scoped per client / workspace
- Assets persist across projects and tasks

---

## 3. Non-Goals

This feature will **not**:
- Replace full DAM systems (e.g. Bynder, Brandfolder)
- Include advanced image editing
- Include real-time collaboration or commenting on files
- Automatically sync with external drives (Google Drive, Dropbox)
- Perform AI-based tagging or analysis (for now)

---

## 4. User Roles

### Client User
- Upload assets
- View and download assets
- Delete assets they uploaded (subject to permissions)
- Organize assets using folders or categories

### Consultant User
- View and download all client assets
- Upload assets on behalf of client (e.g. generated creatives)
- Cannot delete client-uploaded assets unless explicitly allowed

### Admin (Internal)
- Full access across all clients
- Can manage permissions and override deletions

---

## 5. User Stories

### Client
- As a client, I want to upload my brand assets once so I don’t have to resend them repeatedly.
- As a client, I want to know consultants are using the correct, latest files.
- As a client, I want to organize assets so they’re easy to find later.

### Consultant
- As a consultant, I want quick access to approved client assets so I can work efficiently.
- As a consultant, I want to upload deliverables and assets back into the same system.

---

## 6. Functional Requirements

### 6.1 Asset Upload
- Supported file types:
  - Images: `.png`, `.jpg`, `.jpeg`, `.svg`, `.webp`
  - Documents: `.pdf`
  - Fonts: `.ttf`, `.otf`, `.woff`, `.woff2`
- Max file size: configurable (default 50 MB)
- Multiple file upload supported
- Drag-and-drop and file picker

